# Frontend Conventions

- Framework is Nuxt 3 + Vue + Tailwind. Prefer project utilities/components over adding a UI library.
- Keep page files focused on data flow and layout. Extract repeated UI into `frontend/components/**`.
- Put reusable Vue logic in `frontend/composables/**`; put pure reusable logic in `@333fm/utils`.
- Keep `frontend/utils/**` as frontend-facing adapters, auto-import helpers, symbols, and UI-specific formatters.
- Do not put browser, Vue, Nuxt, Tailwind class, or i18n logic into `packages/utils`.
- Components should use existing button/card/form patterns before creating new variants.
- Use auto-imported Nuxt helpers consistently with existing code; avoid unnecessary explicit imports for project auto-imports.
- For styling details, follow `frontend-ui-style.mdc`.
